transcription: This is World Coffee Expert James Hoffman and he taught me the absolute best way to make filter coffee which I use every day. Step 1 grind 18 grams of beans or use 18 grams of ground coffee. Step 2 get out your clever dripper a fantastic $15 gadget that makes way better coffee than way more expensive options. Step 3 put the filter paper in and fill it up with 300 ml of boiling water preferably filtered. Step 4 pour in the ground coffee and give it a stir and then wait for three minutes. Step 5 place the clever dripper on your coffee mug, the contraption engages and causes the coffee to drip through and enjoy your cup of absolutely amazing coffee.

Three of the worst mistakes you can make when buying your first car. Number one, not going in at the end of the month towards the end of the day. Most dealerships have sales targets they need to hit. Number two, going in on a Saturday. That's their busiest day. Losing one sale won't bother them. Number three, telling them you're paying cash. Most of them make their money through finance, so wait till you've got the final price.
